'''Mounted lightsaber combat''' was practiced when [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]] and [[Sith/Legends|Sith]] alike would have to use their [[Lightsaber/Legends|lightsabers]] in combat while riding a mount such as a [[Tauntaun/Legends|tauntaun]], or mounted on a mechanical means of transportation, like a [[Swoop/Legends|swoop]] bike.

==Description==
[[File:Tauntaun_academy.jpg|thumb|left|[[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]] [[Jaden Korr]] cutting down an [[Imperial Remnant]] [[Cold assault stormtrooper|snowtrooper]] on [[Hoth/Legends|Hoth]], while riding a [[Tauntaun/Legends|tauntaun]] during the crisis of the [[Disciples of Ragnos]].]]
In this type of [[Lightsaber combat/Legends|lightsaber combat]], the [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]] and [[Sith/Legends|Sith]] would normally use one hand only, the other hand steering the mount. It would typically consist of simple attacks lashing out at grounded enemy units. Such attacks were normally low lunges with the [[Lightsaber/Legends|lightsaber]] of a diagonal semi-circular nature, as the Jedi and Sith &mdash;being on a mount&mdash;would naturally be elevated in relation to the target. Thus there were some common features between mounted lightsaber combat and the airborne [[Trispzest]] lightsaber combat system, the difference being that in mounted lightsaber combat, the Jedi had much less freedom of movement.

The Jedi could also use the lightsaber to incapacitate other mounted units, by lashing out at either the mount, which was efficient especially if the enemy unit was riding a swoop bike, or the rider himself. Finally, the Jedi could use the lightsaber to deflect blaster shots and the like, thus protecting himself or herself while riding the mount.

==Applications==
[[File:Kybuckcharge_cw1.jpg|thumb|right|180px|[[Yoda/Legends|Yoda]] on his [[Kybuck/Legends|kybuck]] in one of the many battles of the [[Clone Wars/Legends|Clone Wars]].]]
[[Tott Doneeta]] and [[Ulic Qel-Droma/Legends|Ulic]] and [[Cay Qel-Droma]] ignited their lightsabers while charging on [[boma]]s into [[Oron Kira]]'s citadel, but never got to use them upon finding out that that [[Princess/Legends|Princess]] [[Galia]] was marrying Kira willingly.

[[Darth Bane/Legends|Darth Bane]], while riding a [[drexl]] from [[Dxun/Legends|Dxun]] to [[Onderon/Legends|Onderon]], encountered a band of [[Beast Riders]] from the [[Skelda clan]]. It wasn't until the first enemy mount fell that he drew his [[Darth Bane's lightsaber/Legends|weapon]] to deflect [[Blaster/Legends|blasterfire]] from the remaining Riders.

[[Darth Maul/Legends|Darth Maul]] had wielded his [[Darth Maul's double-bladed lightsaber/Legends|saberstaff]] while riding his Sith [[FC-20 speeder bike/Legends|speeders]] on two separate missions on [[Ralltiir/Legends|Ralltiir]] and in combat with [[Battlemaster/Legends|Jedi Battlemaster]] [[Anoon Bondara]], followed shortly after by his ambush on a [[Coruscant Security Force/Legends|Coruscant Security Force]] patrol. During the [[Siege of Otoh Gunga|Naboo Swamp Battle]], he briefly rode a [[Single Trooper Aerial Platform|STAP]] as he charged at [[Boss/Legends|Boss]] [[Ganne]]'s [[Gungan/Legends|Gungan]] forces.

During the [[First Battle of Geonosis/Legends|Battle of Geonosis]], [[Anakin Skywalker/Legends|Anakin Skywalker]] jumped on a transport commandeered by [[Padmé Amidala/Legends|Padmé Amidala]] and used this form of combat while driving by many [[Battle droid/Legends|battle droids]].

In [[Battle of unidentified planet (Yoda's charge)|one]] of the major battles of the [[Clone Wars/Legends|Clone Wars]], [[Yoda/Legends|Yoda]] could be seen on a [[Kybuck/Legends|kybuck]] leading his army of [[Cloning/Legends|clones]] and [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]] into battle. [[Yoda's kybuck]] participated in many battles.

During the [[Battle of Muunilinst/Legends|Battle of Muunilinst]], [[Obi-Wan Kenobi/Legends|Obi-Wan Kenobi]] faced [[Durge/Legends|Durge]] riding a [[Swoop/Legends|swoop]] bike, using his lightsaber to destroy Durge's swoop.

[[Ahsoka Tano/Legends|Ahsoka Tano]] briefly used her lightsaber while chasing [[Aurra Sing/Legends|Aurra Sing]] in the canyons of [[Florrum/Legends|Florrum]]. Both were riding [[Starhawk speeder bike/Legends|Starhawk speeder bikes]].

[[File:Kenobi-and-Durge.png|thumb|left|200px|Obi-Wan Kenobi engages Durge on a speeder bike]]
Yoda engaged the [[Confederacy of Independent Systems/Legends|Separatist]] armies mounted on his [[Kybuck/Legends|kybuck]] during [[General/Legends|General]] [[Grievous/Legends|Grievous]]' [[Battle of Coruscant/Legends|daring attempt]] to kidnap [[Supreme Chancellor/Legends|Supreme Chancellor]] [[Palpatine/Legends|Palpatine]]. Elsewhere in the battle, [[Mace Windu/Legends|Mace Windu]] personally commandeered a [[Vulture-class starfighter|Vulture droid]] immediately after his [[Mace Windu's Eta-2 Actis-class interceptor|starfighter]] was destroyed; he used his right hand to yank the cranial wires, while using his left to both utilize his lightsaber and the Force against the enemy fighters.

In the [[Battle of Utapau/Legends|Battle of Utapau]], Obi-Wan Kenobi chased General Grievous' [[Tsmeu-6 personal wheel bike|wheel bike]] riding a [[Varactyl/Legends|varactyl]]&mdash;named [[Boga/Legends|Boga]]&mdash;using the general's own [[Electrostaff/Legends|electrostaff]] to attack his wheelbike. While not using his lightsaber (which he had lost), Obi-Wan did use the staff in much the same way that he would have used a lightsaber.

[[Jaden Korr]], apprentice to [[Kyle Katarn]] in [[Luke Skywalker/Legends|Luke Skywalker's]] [[New Jedi Order]] may possibly have been mounted on a [[Tauntaun/Legends|tauntaun]] while engaging [[Cold assault stormtrooper|snowtroopers]] on a mission to [[Hoth/Legends|Hoth]].

On a mission to [[Zonju V]], Korr rode a swoop bike, was attacked by several [[Mercenary/Legends|mercenaries]] on swoops, many of which he killed using mounted lightsaber combat techniques.

==Behind the scenes==
Another scene of the [[Battle of Utapau/Legends|Battle of Utapau]] was in the making in animatics. [[Obi-Wan Kenobi/Legends|Obi-Wan Kenobi]] starts chasing General Grievous's wheel bike riding [[Boga/Legends|Boga]], and he uses his [[Lightsaber/Legends|lightsaber]] to destroy two droids. This scene did not make it into the film.

Also, during the Battle of Utapau, Obi-Wan Kenobi uses his lightsaber to block oncoming [[Blaster/Legends|blaster]] bolts while riding Boga. This is another example of mounted lightsaber combat.

In ''[[Star Wars: Jedi Knight: Jedi Academy]]'' during the [[Mission to Hoth (Jaden Korr)|Mission to Hoth]] it is possible (through the use of force speed) to obtain a Tauntaun and use it in the duel with [[Alora (Dark Jedi)|Alora]], however as the cut screens show [[Jaden Korr]] fighting Alora on foot regardless, meaning this is non-canon.

